The national government has released Sh100 million for refurbishment of hospitals in Lamu county. President Uhuru Kenyatta last year pledged to release Sh200 milion to upgrade the facilities.Early last year, the national government released the first Sh100 million, which was used to build an ICU, an accident and emergency unit, a modern theatre and renal unit at the King Fahad County Hospital.Speaking in his office on Tuesday, Health executive Mohamed Kombo said the money will be used to upgrade Mpeketoni and Faza subcounty hospitals, which are expected to be elevated to level four status. &ldquo;Sh50 million will put up a modern maternity and children&rsquo;s wing at the Mpeketoni Hospital,&rdquo; he said.